1. COMPETENCY OVERVIEW
==================================================
 
Competency:        First Contact — はじめの一歩
Level:             Super Beginner (Pre-A1 → A1)
Weeks:             1–8 (within the student's personal counter)
Total prompts:     224 (56 per purpose)
Delivery method:   Daily LINE message, personal student timetable
 
CORE SKILL:
Starting a conversation naturally without freezing.
 
STUDENT PROFILE AT THIS LEVEL:
- Freezes when spoken to in English
- Knows individual words but cannot connect them in real time
- Highly anxious about making mistakes
- Needs encouragement, heavy scaffolding, and early wins
- Expected response: 1–2 sentences maximum
 
JAPANESE SUPPORT LEVEL: Full (●●●●●)
Includes: vocabulary translations, grammar explanations, cultural
context, pronunciation tips (odd Weeks 1/3/5/7 Day 1), prior
knowledge bridge sentences (Weeks 3/5/7 Day 1), motivational
notes, competency goal summary (Week 1 Day 1 only).
 
COMPETENCY GOAL (communicated to student on Day 1):
By Week 8, students will be able to:
- Greet naturally in their purpose context (Good morning! / Hey! / Excuse me!)
- Give a real, specific answer beyond "Good!" or "Fine"
- Ask a specific question back
- Close a short conversation naturally
 
 
