2. 8-WEEK THEME ARC
==================================================
 
Theme structure: 4 themes × 2 weeks each.
Each theme builds on the previous one.
 
Weeks 1–2: Natural greetings
  Focus: Opening a conversation — how to say hello in context
  Key phrases:
    Work:    "Morning!" / "How's it going?" / "Hi there!"
    Hobby:   "Hey!" / "Nice to meet you!" / "Good to see you!"
    Travel:  "Excuse me!" / "Hi there!" / "Small world!"
    Casual:  "Hey!" / "Oh hey!" / "You look familiar!"
  Grammar:  "How's..." contractions (Week 2)
  Vocabulary: context-specific greetings (Week 1 Day 3),
              re-encounter greetings (Week 2 Day 3)
  By end of Week 2: student can open a conversation naturally
 
Weeks 3–4: Real answers
  Focus: Giving genuine, specific answers — beyond "Fine/Good"
  Key phrases:
    Work:    "I just finished..." / "Pretty good! I just..."
    Hobby:   "Really enjoying it!" / "A bit challenging but fun!"
    Travel:  "Absolutely loving it!" / "A bit exhausting but worth it!"
    Casual:  "I'm really into..." / "I've been..."
  Grammar:  "just" for recent actions (Week 3), "a bit" for balance (Week 4)
  Vocabulary: feeling words for context (Week 3 Day 3)
  By end of Week 4: student can give a real, specific answer
 
Weeks 5–6: First questions back
  Focus: Asking a specific question after answering — keeping it alive
  Key phrases:
    Work:    "How about you — how's your week been going?"
    Hobby:   "How about you — what's your favorite part?"
    Travel:  "Have you tried the local food yet?"
    Casual:  "Have you been to any good events lately?"
  Grammar:  "Have you...yet?" (Week 6)
  Vocabulary: Spaced Recall Day on Week 5 Day 3 (no new vocab)
  By end of Week 6: student can answer AND ask something back
 
Weeks 7–8: Mini conversations
  Focus: Putting it all together — open, exchange, close
  Key phrases:
    Work:    "Talk later!" / "Have a good one!" / "Let's catch up!"
    Hobby:   "Have fun!" / "Let's catch up after!"
    Travel:  "Safe travels!" / "Let's compare notes!"
    Casual:  "Let's hang out!" / "So great meeting you!"
  Grammar:  3-part conversation formula (Week 8 Day 2)
  Vocabulary: Spaced Recall Day on Week 7 Day 3 (no new vocab),
              Full toolkit summary on Week 8 Day 3
  By end of Week 8: student can have a complete mini conversation
 
 
