4. 7-DAY PEDAGOGICAL ARC (C1 SPECIFICS)
==================================================
 
Day 1 — Listening Practice
  Format: [Listen] + 2–4 [Voice] lines to hear and repeat + [*] note
  Purpose-specific dialogues per week
  Week 1 includes: competency goals summary in Japanese support
  Odd weeks (1,3,5,7) include: [Pronunciation] note in Japanese support
  Odd weeks (3,5,7) include: prior knowledge bridge in Japanese support
  Response type: voice_short
  Audio: pre-recorded M4A required (see Section 7)
 
Day 2 — Grammar Tip
  Format: [Tip] + 3 examples + >> insight note + [Practice] instruction
  Week 1: Example answer provided
  Weeks 2+: No example (student uses own words)
  Response type: text
 
Day 3 — Vocabulary / Recall Day
  Weeks 1–4, 6, 8: [Practice] + 3 phrases in context + written practice
  Weeks 5 & 7: [Recall] — retrieve prior phrases without looking back
  Response type: text
  DB type field: "Vocabulary" (Wks 1-4,6,8) / "Recall Day" (Wks 5,7)
 
Day 4 — Speaking Prompt
  Format: [Challenge] + scenario context + scaffold options + [Voice]
  Week 1: includes [Example] model answer
  Weeks 2+: scaffold only, no example
  Week 6 Day 4 (Prompt #39): student initiates the conversation first,
    other person responds, student then reacts and asks back
  Response type: voice_short
 
Day 5 — Quiz
  Format: [Quiz] + scenario + A/B options + combined instruction
  Single-message format: student sends choice + reason + own version
  Answer pattern: BBAABABA (see Section 6)
  correct_answer and quiz_explanation stored in DB for teacher reference
  Response type: choice
 
Day 6 — Real Talk
  Format: [Scenario] + situation setup + response instructions
  Teacher responds personally within the day
  Weeks 2–8: response window message included
  Response type: voice_short
 
Day 7 — Free Speaking
  Format: [Challenge] + open prompt
  Week 1: no feedback loop line (no prior feedback exists)
  Weeks 2–7: includes "If I gave you feedback last time — try to use it!"
  Week 4 (Prompt #28): metacognitive reflection questions in Japanese
  Week 8 (Prompt #56): metacognitive reflection + achievement checklist
  Response type: voice_free
 
 
