9. CONTENT NOTES & DECISIONS
==================================================
 
PROMPT #39 (Week 6 Day 4) — Speaking Prompt
  Decision: Student initiates the conversation first by asking how
  things are going. The other person responds positively. The student
  then reacts and asks a specific question back.
  Rationale: More natural than having the other person open with a
  positive statement unprompted. Student initiating = realistic scenario.
  Purpose-specific openers:
    Work:    "Ask your coworker how their week is going"
    Hobby:   "Ask your classmate how they've been enjoying the class"
    Travel:  "Ask a fellow traveler what they think of the place so far"
    Casual:  "Ask a new friend how things have been going for them"
 
PROMPT #42 (Week 6 Day 7) — Free Speaking
  The prompt is delivered as an automated third-person scenario
  ("Your coworker/classmate/fellow traveler/friend says: ...").
  No manual LINE message required from the teacher.
  The scenario line is part of the automated prompt_text.
 
PROMPT #28 (Week 4 Day 7) — Metacognitive Reflection
  The reflection questions live in prompt_text_japanese only.
  prompt_text contains the English speaking challenge as normal.
  This prevents Japanese characters appearing in the English field
  and prevents display issues on teacher portal.
 
PROMPT #56 (Week 8 Day 7) — Module Final Challenge
  Contains both the final speaking challenge AND the achievement
  checklist AND the two metacognitive reflection questions.
  All Japanese content (checklist + reflection) in prompt_text_japanese.
  English field contains the speaking challenge only.
 
DAY 3 TYPE FIELD VALUES
  Weeks 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 8: type = "Vocabulary"
  Weeks 5, 7:              type = "Recall Day"
  This distinction is used by the edge function and teacher portal.
 
JAPANESE SUPPORT IN PROMPT_TEXT
  The >> marker in prompt_text_japanese separates sections visually.
  The [Pronunciation] and [Reflection] tags are content markers only —
  they are not converted to emoji by the edge function.
  Japanese support is always in prompt_text_japanese, NEVER in
  prompt_text. Mixing languages in prompt_text causes display issues.
 
RESPONSE WINDOW (Day 6 & 7)
  From Week 2 onward, Day 6 and Day 7 prompts include a note that
  the teacher will respond. This is a commitment and must be honoured.
  Day 5 quiz responses are reference-only for the teacher — no
  personal reply required, only if the student asks follow-up questions.
 
 
